OL,3,CEx-Post Office boss accused staff of
OL,4,Chaving 'hands in the till', inquiry
OL,5,Ctold
OL,7,F"'It had gone to court' was the
OL,8,Fexpression used and I had not
OL,9,Fencountered the notion of an
OL,10,Forganisation that could make that
OL,11,Fdecision on it's own."
OL,13,FCounsel to the inquiry, Sam Stevens
OL,14,Fasked: "Your evidence is still that in
OL,15,Fno point in the years that you were
OL,16,Fthe managing director, (nobody) in the
OL,17,Fsecurity or investigations team raised
OL,18,Fthe fact that they made decisions to
OL,19,Fprosecute?"
