OL,3,CEx-Post Office boss accused staff of
OL,4,Chaving 'hands in the till', inquiry
OL,5,Ctold
OL,7,FMr Castleton, whose story was
OL,8,Fhighlighted in ITV drama Mr Bates vs
OL,9,FThe Post Office, declared bankruptcy
OL,10,Fafter losing the case and was left
OL,11,Fwith costs of #321,000.
OL,13,FMr Stevens asked: "Did you not to
OL,14,Fthink to ask why there was such a
OL,15,Fsignificant spend on one case?"
OL,17,FMr Cook replied: "I just don't
OL,18,Frecall... I can't think why I wouldn't
OL,19,Fand so either it was a mistake on my
OL,20,Fpart or it wasn't in the report, I
OL,21,Fdon't know."
OL,26,@uD@SOUwD@_O]yD@ROU}D@LO]
